title: For Sale/Trade:  QUALITY 9mm and .22 LR for ... ?
postcontent:
Ok, my fellow Americans, here's the deal.  Due to the current political climate and the high prevalence of sheeple, I just paid a hell of a lot more than I should have to for another 'black rifle.'  I'm not made of fiat currency, so therefore I need to offset my latest endeavor into common sense.

Unlike most folks selling their ammo you will see I'm actually offering high QUALITY products at a premium ... vs all the entry-level products at ridiculous mark-ups ... that are all over the place out there.  Am I charging more than I paid?  Yup.  I'm fully justified to do so due to the fact that I had the foresight to plan and ACT accordingly.  I jumped through plenty of hoops to get what I have.  I don't make it a habit to give away any of my labors for nothing in return, at least in this instance  Try going anywhere online or elsewhere and see if you can find a better deal on what I have to offer.  Most everything I'm offering isn't even readily available these days... and hasn't been for quite some months now.  Period.

It's been my experience that firearms related PURCHASES always turn out to be a most positive and beneficial thing, whereas whenever I've SOLD something I already possessed ... down the road I seriously regretted it.  Always.  So as crazy as it might sound, if I don't sell one solitary round, that would actually work out for me in 'the long run.'  Just ask Don.  If I TRY to replace anything I'm offering here within the next 6-12 months or even later ... most likely I'll be paying more than what you'd be paying to me in the present.  Of course that is assuming that these type of QUALITY products ... will even be readily available for purchase at that time.

Are you receiving my signal?

Due to MY inaction (and stupidity) as to not stockpiling enough 'black rifles' ... that's where I'm feeling the pain.  It bites like a vicious beast.  I dropped the ball ... same as you ... just in a different facet of preparedness.  If you really want to jack up my game plan ... you might be sportin' an M variety SKS (accepts AK mags) or maybe even a Type 56 in good condition.  I digs me some SKSs.  No ducks.  You also might be the proud owner of a Ruger Mark II with a bull barrel.  I could use one of those for the kitchen.  I dig working man's steel, so you could also hold sway over me with a... wait for it ... EAA Windicator 357 Mag, preferably the new and improved model.  Hell, I might even entertain a WASR but no dice if you're looking to score $1000 in trade for it.  Reasonably affordable and QUALITY AK 'type' rifles are like memorable girlfriends, one can never have too many in life.  Take care of them and they'll take care of you.  Be reasonable and I'll act in kind.  If you have a QUALITY piece that is understandably marked up some, I may bite.  It you're slangin' cheap studge ... and marking it up into the stratosphere, I'm going to ponder your significance to society and your relevant importance to my life personally.  Just to round things out for both sides, I could possibly use more 7.62x39 or 7.62x54R.  I dig sealed surplus and love those Russian crates full of steel business cards.  Also ... I actually help out squirrels with their food storage and if I ever so much as thought of hurting one, even in a dream ... I'd wake up and apologize to my neighbors in my avocado tree.  So ... you can keep the 5.56, I'm not the type to break a heel in a rush or never admit I'm wrong ... or get my rocks off by killin' fuzzies in an effort ... to compensate for something.  My apologies if my tastes offend the masses. 

Kinda.

So, ladies and gentlemen ... that's the car I'm drivin.'  I'm right next to you in the thick of it.  I don't see any lanes opening up any time soon.  I'm just as pissed at (and screwed by) the current state of affairs in our country, a country that no longer resembles the one I was born into and grew up in (hangin' out on The Rez in the 70s and down the road was so much more palatable).

It is what it is.

I voted for Ron Paul and Gary Johnson ...

Let's dance in public so as to take steps to avoid any toe steppin' by impolite types.  If you have a gun shop in my area that will accommodate our transaction that is fine by me.

Always.  So as crazy as it might sound, if I don't sell one solitary round, that would actually work out for me in 'the long run.'  Just ask Don. title: For Sale:  Kel-tec KSG
postcontent:
The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

I have the box, sling, paperwork and just added a fore-grip. Gun has had 30 rounds run through it. 

Call or text REDACTED before 11pm. Cash only.
